    •  Decreases the cost of aircraft ownership.

- Former AOPA Member, memberservices@aopa.org?cc=Jim Coon <Jim.Coon@aopa.org>,Mark Baker <mark@aopa.org>,Ken Mead <Ken.Mead@aopa.org>,Timothy Fortune <Timothy.Fortune@aopa.org>,Thomas Haines <Thomas.Haines@aopa.org>,Jiri Marousek <Jiri.Marousek@aopa.org>,Katie Pribyl <Katie.Pribyl@aopa.org>,Erica Saccoia <Erica.Saccoia@aopa.org>&bcc=Flytenow <aopa@flytenow.com>&subject=AOPA should support online flight-sharing and the revised Aviation Empowerment Act.&body=Attn: Jim Coon, SVP Government Affairs & Advocacy

AOPA,

As a member of AOPA and supporter of General Aviation, I am extremely frustrated and disappointed to hear that AOPA is lobbying against and blocking the revised Aviation Empowerment Act (S. 2650), as it is undeniably pro-General Aviation.

The revised bill:  
    •  Does NOT allow for "Uber-like" companies. It only allows pilots to communicate for pro-rata flight-sharing by communicating their flights to find a passenger with a common purpose.
    •  No negative impact on safety. Pilots have been flight-sharing using public bulletin boards for decades, this just brings the same practice into the 21st century.
    •  Decreases the cost of aircraft ownership.
    •  Promotes safety by allowing pilots to keep their skills current.
    •  Stimulates economies at regional airports and FBOs.
    •  Brings the U.S. in line with the European Aviation Safety Agency, who embraced flight sharing years ago.

By opposing the revised Aviation Empowerment Act, and instead, suggesting the language of Section 516 of H.R. 4, AOPA is giving more power to the FAA to limit pilot communication and delaying the advancement of flight-sharing by requesting a report when flight sharing is already thriving in Europe.

AOPA should immediately stop lobbying the Senate to block the revised Aviation Empowerment Act, and instead, publicly support flight-sharing via open communication to find a passenger with a common purpose and the revised bill.

Sincerely,
AOPA Member, press@flytenow.com
